{{Infobox University |name = Euroinnova Business School |type = [[Private school|Private]] |established = 2000 |city = Granada |country = Spain |students = 25.000 per year |website = [http://www.euroinnova.us/ Euroinnova USA][http://www.euroinnova.edu.es/ Cursos Online] }}
'''Euroinnova''' is a business school specializing in further education, online courses, distance learning courses, accredited courses up to master's degrees. It was founded in 2000 in [[Granada]] (Spain), and currently based in USA and has a presence in six countries in Latin America: Argentina, Chile, Colombia, Mexico, Peru and Venezuela.
== Students ==
As part of its 14th anniversary, Euroinnova Business School conducted a study on the scope and international presence of online education. INDIZE produced a detailed report on all students taking into consideration nationality, study sector, sex, age, city, their level of education, etc. The study shows that Euroinnova in 2014 reached 150 000 pupils divided into more than 70 different nationalities. Since 2010 they have been enrolled on average more than 25,000 students per year. In the USA Euroinnova has over a hundred students.<ref>[http://www.indize.es/publicaciones/ "Euroinnova Business School Report by INDIZE"] ''INDIZE''</ref>
== Certifications ==
Euroinnova Business School is an associated member of the International Commission on Distance Education (UNESCO), and collaborates with the Spanish Professional Association of Naturopathy and Biotherapy (APENB).<ref>[http://www.apenb.org/web/index.php/noticias-apenb/437-convenio-con-euroinnova-business-school "Colaboración Euroinnova Formación con la Asociación Profesional Española de Naturopatía y Bioterapia"] ''Spanish Professional Association of Naturopathy and Biotherapy (APENB)''</ref> Euroinnova is also Institutional Member of the Spanish Society of Education (SEP) and features Trust Mark Online.<ref>[https://www.confianzaonline.es/empresas/euroinnova.htm "Trust Mark Online"] ''Confianza Online''</ref>
