'''Gabriele Kaiser''' is a German [[mathematics education|mathematics educator]]. She is a professor of mathematics education at the [[University of Hamburg]].

Kaiser completed a doctorate in 1986 and a [[habilitation]] in 1997 at the [[University of Kassel]].{{r|cv}} Her doctoral dissertation, ''Anwendungen im Mathematikunterricht - Konzeptionen und Untersuchungen zur unterrichtlichen Realisierung'', was supervised by Werner Blum.{{r|mgp}} She became a professor at Hamburg in 1998, and served as vice dean of education from 2010 to 2016.{{r|cv}} Since 2005 she has been editor-in-chief of the journal ''ZDM Mathematics Education'',{{r|cv|zdm}} and she is the editor or co-editor of 28 books on mathematics education.{{r|books}}

Kaiser was a speaker at the 2002 [[International Congress of Mathematicians]].{{r|icm}}
In 2012, a [[festschrift]] was published in her honor.{{r|mkr}}

