The '''General Scholastic Ability Test''' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: 大學學科能力測驗 [[Pinyin]]: Dàxué xuékē nénglì cèyàn)<ref name="General Scholastic">''China Post'' [http://www.chinapost.com.tw/taiwan/national/national-news/2015/02/02/427986/General-Scholastic.htm General Scholastic Ability Test commences]  Chi-hao James Lo, 2 February 2015</ref> is the [[Education in Taiwan|Taiwanese]] university [[List of admission tests to colleges and universities|entrance exam]]. The test is administered over two days; subjects include [[Mandarin Chinese]], English, Mathematics, sciences (Chemistry, Biology, Physics, Geology), and Humanities (History,Geography, Civics &Law).<ref name="General Scholastic" /> In recent years,{{When|date=March 2016}} the test has attempted to encourage students to read outside of their classwork and  be attuned to current events by including questions related to the [[Ebola virus]], [[climate change]],<ref>''Asia One'' [http://news.asiaone.com/news/asia/taiwans-general-scholastic-ability-test-commences Taiwan's General Scholastic Ability Test commences] 2 February 2015</ref> [[3G]] technology, and [[Spider-Man]].<ref>''China Post'' [http://www.chinapost.com.tw/taiwan/national/national-news/2015/02/03/428062/General-Scholastic.htm General Scholastic Ability Test English exams hardest in 5 years] Chi-hao James Lo, 3 February 2015</ref><ref>BBC News [https://www.bbc.com/news/business-35614030 Top 10 exam rituals from stressed students across Asia], Jody-Lan Castle</ref>

